<br>
Her daughter, Abysinthe stood by her side. Her wicked, always handsome Xaizael looming - his features pensive and distraught.<br>
<br>
Hunger was unleashed in a whirlwind; sated the beast slept. <br>
<br>
------------<br>
<br>
Morning sounds roused the slumbering leagues within the dark city. Bustling along the hallways and passages that she'd always known. Chain gloved fingers crawled over a passing wall as she started down the passage towards third gate. Nobles at her heels and nipping, calling out praises to her. It only irritated her, and she'd suffer it. A hand shot upwards to hault their stammering and questioning.<br>
<br>
The library..the Tavern..<br>
<br>
She headed into the small tavern where the troll stood and eyed all the occupants within, those who followed her made to stand without, save her Daughter and Xaizael. Gloves were slid from her fingers with firm plucking movements. Silvers crawled over faces and figures that lounged, only startled by the high booted kick of a heel to the door in a gust like slam.<br>
<br>
&quot;Vendui abbilen..&quot;<br>
<br>
She was back. It felt good.  <p>Ciennaa Vlos'yorn<br>
Ilharess of Black Oath.<br>
Yathrin of Innoruuk.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hate the seed in which we sow. Planted proper it will grow. Come the rain or come the snow. The blood will come to reap it.&quot;<br>
